97
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,920
Because to follow your instincts...

98
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:03,000
and to inspire your men by your example...

99
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:08,930
you have to be with them where the metal meets the meat.

100
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:12,560
Sergeant-Major Plumley made all four combat jumps...

101
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:15,180
in the 82nd Airborne during World War II.

102
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:17,350
Sicily, Salerno, Normandy...

103
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:20,480
and Holland, plus one more in Korea.

104
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,490
He answers to me and to me alone.

105
00:11:25,570 --> 00:11:28,490
Now, I hope you gentlemen like training...

106
00:11:28,570 --> 00:11:30,910
'cause me and the sergeant-major

107
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:34,080
we love it.

108
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:39,710
Three strikes and you're not out!

109
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:42,710
There is always one more thing you can do.

110
00:11:53,890 --> 00:11:55,310
Here we go, boys.

111
00:11:55,390 --> 00:11:57,640
Move! Move! Go! Now!

112
00:11:57,730 --> 00:11:59,850
- Two. - Let's go!

113
00:11:59,940 --> 00:12:01,860
Three.

114
00:12:01,940 --> 00:12:03,320
We're outta here!

115
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,440
- Pretty good, huh? - Pretty good.

116
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:10,660
There's only one thing wrong.

117
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:15,040
Be sharp! We will be the best platoon in this battalion!

118
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:17,540
Be ready in there! Let's go! Let's go!

119
